<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>chance one’s arm • one would give his right arm</xh5><p> <i>chance one’s arm—</i>do smth. in the face of probable failure; take one’s chance of doing smth. successfully: He <u>chanced his arm</u> in pursuit of a world record and for a while looked like he might just pull it off.</p><p> <i>one would give his right arm</i>—(hyperbolic) one is ready to give up his most valuable possession (to achieve smth.): I’m sure Leon <u>would give his right arm</u> for a fraction of John’s success.</p> </entry>
